{{Infobox politician | name = Anna Šabatová | image = Anna Šabatová at Duha nad Brnem Opening Party 2001a.jpg | caption = Šabatová in 2001 | office = Ombudsman of the Czech Republic | term_start = 18 February 2014 | term_end = | predecessor = [[Pavel Varvařovský]] | successor = | birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1951|6|23|df=y}} | birth_place = [[Brno]], Czechoslovakia }} '''Anna Šabatová''' (born 23 June 1951) is a Czech politician, who is the current [[Ombudsman#Czech Republic|ombudsman]] of the [[Czech Republic]]. She was a signatory to [[Charter 77]] and its spokesperson in 1986. Šabatová was awarded the [[United Nations Prize in the Field of Human Rights]] in 1998. She received the [[Medal of Merit (Czech Republic)|Czech Medal of Merit]] (First Grade) in 2002.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hrad.cz/en/czech-republic/state-decorations/medal-of-merit/list|title=List of Honoured|date=n.d.|work=hrad.cz|accessdate=28 September 2017}}</ref> In 2014, Šabatová was elected as the ombudsman of the Czech Republic, replacing [[Pavel Varvařovský]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.radio.cz/en/section/bulletin/news--3614|title=Šabatová to be new Ombudsman|date=14 February 2014|work=[[Radio Prague]]|accessdate=28 September 2017}}</ref>
