{{about||the scientist with the same name|Cosimo Commisso (scientist)|the Canadian soccer player with the same name|Cosimo Commisso (soccer)}}
'''Cosimo Commisso''' (born 6 February 1950 in Siderno), also known as "the quail" ("'u quagghia"), is an [[Italy|Italian]] criminal and a member of the [['Ndrangheta]], a mafia-type organization in [[Calabria]]. He belongs to and was the boss of the [[Commisso 'ndrina]] based in [[Siderno]] with his cousin [[Antonio Commisso]] and his brother Rocco Commisso.<ref name=np300705>[http://www.canada.com/national/nationalpost/news/story.html?id=9af45529-0622-4e8e-be40-ebfc4c7a4f2b Back to the 'wolves'], National Post July 30, 2005</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thestar.com/news/gta/2018/03/26/drug-smuggling-mobsters-used-retired-police-dogs-to-help-secure-cargo-court-hears.html|title=Drug-smuggling mobsters used retired police dogs to help secure cargo, court hears|publisher=thestar.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://nationalpost.com/news/world/alleged-toronto-area-mafia-leaders-named-as-suspects-in-massive-italian-crime-probe|title=Alleged Toronto-area Mafia leaders named as suspects in massive Italian crime probe|date=30 September 2015|publisher=nationalpost.com}}</ref>
He took over the reins of the clan from his father [[Francesco Commisso]], who had been the right-hand man of the historical 'Ndrangheta boss of Siderno, [[Antonio Macrì]].<ref name=np300705 /><ref name=gds151210>{{it icon}} [http://www.gazzettadelsud.it/NotiziaArchivio.aspx?art=168190&Edizione=7&A=20101216 È Giuseppe "u mastru" il vero erede di Ntoni Macrì], Gazzetta del Sud, December 15, 2010</ref>
The Commisso 'ndrina has a branch in Canada, in the [[Greater Toronto Area]], which is part of the wider [[Siderno Group]].<ref name=tts081209>[https://www.thestar.com/news/gta/article/735623 Corruption probe: The clubs], The Toronto Star, December 8, 2009</ref>
In the 1980s the [[Buffalo crime family]] also operated in Toronto and [[Hamilton, Ontario|Hamilton]], and hired [[Satan's Choice MC]] [[hitman]] Cecil Kirby to kill [[Pietro Scarcella]] and [[Paul Volpe (mobster)|Paul Volpe]] in an arrangement with Rocco Remo and Cosimo Commisso to gain more control of the market. However, the plot was foiled when Kirby turned [[Royal Canadian Mounted Police]] informant.<ref name=globe>{{cite web|url=https://www.theglobeandmail.com/news/national/mob-war-led-to-russo-shooting-sources-say/article978951/|title=Mob war led to Russo shooting, sources say|publisher=theglobeandmail.com|date=16 April 2005|accessdate=25 May 2017}}</ref><ref name=schneider330>Schneider, ''Iced: The Story of Organized Crime in Canada'', pp. 330</ref>
He is described as the most notorious member of the group and its former leader, and is currently serving a life sentence in Italy for his involvement with the 'Ndrangheta.<ref name=nathanson>[https://web.archive.org/web/20130621020519/http://www.osgoode.yorku.ca/NathansonBackUp/CurrentEvents/2005_Q2.htm Organized Crime in Canada: A Quarterly Summary, April to June, 2005] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110530061138/http://www.osgoode.yorku.ca/NathansonBackUp/CurrentEvents/2005_Q2.htm |date=2011-05-30 }}, Nathanson Centre on Transnational Human Rights, Crime and Security</ref> The cousin of "The Quail", [[Antonio Commisso]], was on the [[list of most wanted fugitives in Italy]] until his capture on June 28, 2005, in Woodbridge.<ref name=np300705/>
On June 28, 2018, Cosimo Ernesto Commisso, of [[Woodbridge, Ontario]] and an unrelated female were shot and killed. According to sources contacted by the [[Toronto Star]], "Commisso was related to "The Quail" of Siderno, Italy, who has had relations in Ontario, is considered by police to be a "'Ndrangheta organized crime boss".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thestar.com/news/gta/2018/07/02/man-killed-in-woodbridge-shooting-had-family-ties-to-organized-crime.html|title=Man killed in Woodbridge shooting had family ties to organized crime - The Star|publisher=}}</ref> The [[National Post]] reported that Cosimo Ernesto Commisso, while not a known criminal, "shares a name and family ties with a man who has for decades been reputed to be a Mafia leader in the Toronto area".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://nationalpost.com/news/canada/the-less-you-know-the-better-it-is-mob-links-to-shocking-murder-of-man-woman-on-quiet-woodbridge-street|title='The less you know the better it is': Mob links in murder of man, woman on quiet Woodbridge street|date=29 June 2018|publisher=}}</ref>
