{{Infobox adult biography |name = Stephanie Swift |image = Stephanie Swift at AVN Adult Entertainment Expo 2008 1.jpg |image_size = |caption = Stephanie Swift at [[AVN Adult Entertainment Expo|AVN Expo]] 2008 |birth_date = {{birth date and age|1972|2|7}} |birth_place = [[Louisiana]], United States<ref name=AVNprofile>{{cite web|title=Pornstar Profile – Stephanie Swift|url=http://www.avn.com/porn-stars/37665.html|publisher=[[AVN (magazine)|AVN]]|accessdate=February 14, 2010|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090619172523/http://www.avn.com/porn-stars/37665.html|archivedate=June 19, 2009|df=}}</ref> |birthname = |spouse = |death_date = |height = {{height|ft=5|in=1}}<ref name=AVNprofile/> |weight = {{convert|110|lb|kg|abbr=on}}<ref name=AVNprofile/> |alias = China Cat, Melody<ref name=AVNprofile/> |website = }}
'''Stephanie Swift''' (born February 7, 1972) is an American former [[Pornographic film actor|pornographic actress]] who starred in over 300 [[Pornographic film|adult movies]] between 1995 and 2009, when she was diagnosed with [[breast cancer]] and left the industry. She is a member of both the [[List of members of the AVN Hall of Fame|AVN]]<ref name=avn>{{cite web|url=http://www.avnawards.com/halloffame.php|title=AVN Awards Past Winners – HALL OF FAME|accessdate=September 15, 2014|archivedate=April 15, 2009|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090415212412/http://www.avnawards.com/halloffame.php|deadurl=yes|df=}}</ref> and [[XRCO Hall of Fame|XRCO]] Halls of Fame.<ref name=xrco/> Swift now works with [[XXXchurch.com]], a [[Christian]] outreach group that offers to help pornographic actors leave the industry and help compulsive porn users overcome their [[porn addiction]].<ref name=X3text>{{cite web|year=2011|title=Stephanie Swift|url=http://www.xxxchurch.com/stephanie.html|website=xxxchurch.com|publisher=Fireproof Ministries|accessdate=March 15, 2011}}</ref><ref name=X3vid>{{cite AV media|people=Stephanie Swift|year=2011|title=Stephanie Swift: Cancer Saved My Life|url=http://player.subsplash.com/b28dc5e|publisher=XXXchurch via Subsplash|accessdate=September 15, 2014}}</ref>
==Early life== Swift spent her childhood in [[Louisiana]]. She is one-quarter Filipino.<ref name=lim>{{cite book|last=Lim|first=Gerrie|title=In Lust We Trust: Adventures in Adult Cinema|year=2006|publisher=Monsoon Books|isbn=978-981-05-5302-9|page=99}}</ref> Between the ages of one and fourteen, she suffered [[sexual abuse]] at the hands of family members.<ref name=X3vid/> At the age of 19, she lived in [[San Diego, California]] and worked as a [[Striptease|stripper]] for six months at a club called The Body Shop<ref name="About Me">{{cite web|title=Stephanie Swift: About Me |publisher=Official Site of Stephanie Swift |url=http://www.stephanieswift.com/aboutme.php |accessdate=February 14, 2010 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090228204440/http://www.stephanieswift.com/aboutme.php |archivedate=February 28, 2009 }}</ref>
==Career== [[File:Stephanie Swift at Erotica Los Angeles 2001 1.jpg|thumb|upright|left|Stephanie Swift at AVN Expo 2001]] [[File:Stephanie Swift at Sexxxpose Party 2.jpg|thumb|upright=0.85|Stephanie Swift at a party in 2006]] After earning her degree, she posed in [[Fetish model|nude model]]ling photographs for five years and was featured in ''[[Club International]]''.<ref name="About Me"/><ref name=Wickedbio>{{cite web|url=http://www.wickedpictures.com/bio/p-z/Stephanie_Swift.html|title=Wicked Pictures bio|accessdate=February 13, 2010|publisher=[[Wicked Pictures]]|archivedate=February 12, 2010|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100212021142/http://www.wickedpictures.com/bio/p-z/Stephanie_Swift.html|deadurl=yes|df=}}</ref> Swift segued from nude model work to Southern California's [[adult film]] industry, where she began her career in 1995.<ref name="About Me"/> Her first [[Softcore pornography|softcore]] scene was in [[Playboy TV]]'s ''Up Close and Dangerous''.<ref name="About Me"/> Her first [[Hardcore pornography|hardcore]] [[Sex in film|sex scene]] was in ''Space Sirens''.<ref name="About Me"/> She went on to win several awards, including the [[AVN Female Performer of the Year Award]] in 1998.<ref name=awards>{{cite web|url=http://avnawards.avn.com/past/winners/1998|title=1998 AVN Awards Show – History|accessdate=September 15, 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140115041053/http://avnawards.avn.com/past/winners/1998|archivedate=January 15, 2014|deadurl=yes|df=}}</ref> She was, for a period, a contract girl with [[Wicked Pictures]].<ref name="About Me"/>
She has made appearances on the exotic dancing circuit as a featured performer.<ref name=LVstrippers>{{cite web|url=http://www.las-vegas-strippers.net/20Mm04_exotic_dancer_fanfair_review.htm|title=The 2004 Exotic Dancer Fan Fair Review|accessdate=February 14, 2010|publisher=Las Vegas Strippers|df=}}{{dead link|date=January 2018|bot=medic}}{{cbignore|bot=medic}}</ref> In 2004, she launched her own production company called ''Swift Entertainment'', in which she was a [[Film director|director]], [[screenwriter]] and [[Film producer|producer]].<ref name="About Me"/>
Swift was inducted into the AVN Hall of Fame<ref name=avn/> in 2006 and the XRCO Hall of Fame in 2008.<ref name=xrco/>
In 2011, Swift released a video filmed for XXXchurch.com in which she said her cancer had been in remission since March 2010, and she explained her decision to quit the adult film industry. She said the industry gives a "false sense of accomplishment." She is currently working with the church in their efforts to reach out to pornographic film actors.<ref name=X3text/><ref name=X3vid/>
==Personal life==
An August 2009 [[XBIZ]] [[press release]] announced that Swift had been diagnosed with [[breast cancer]] in her left breast and asked for donations to help with her medical bills.<ref name=Hunter090813>{{cite press release|last=Hunter|first=Tod|date=August 13, 2009|title=Performer Stephanie Swift Diagnosed With Breast Cancer|url=http://www.xbiz.com/news/111634 |location=New York|publisher=Adnet Media|accessdate=September 15, 2014}}</ref> Later that month, she had a double [[mastectomy]].<ref name=Rodriguez091009>{{cite press release|last=Rodriguez|first=Ariana|date=October 9, 2009|title=‘Sex at the Shore’ Benefit Set for Tomorrow|url=http://www.xbiz.com/news/113608|location=Long Beach, CA|publisher=Adnet Media|accessdate=October 22, 2009}}</ref> By March 2010, she had completed [[chemotherapy]] and scheduled [[lymph node]] surgery.<ref name=Garrett100303>{{cite press release|last=Garrett|first=Wade|date=March 3, 2010|title=Mile High's Nica Noelle to Host Stephanie Swift Cancer Benefit|url=http://business.avn.com/articles/Mile-High-s-Nica-Noelle-to-Host-Stephanie-Swift-Cancer-Benefit-388312.html|location=Los Angeles|publisher=AVN Media Network|accessdate=March 10, 2010}}</ref>
